Reasoning: The paper deals with optimization problems related to communication channels, specifically the Gaussian arbitrarily varying product channel and the arbitrarily varying channel with colored Gaussian noise. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses a two-player zero-sum game played by the user and the jammer, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of water filling solutions is a common technique in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with power allocation strategies, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI).
